      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy decision table into table J09A_temp where the tour starts with J09A.\\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\\n3. Classify meter reading type. Apply rules: 1. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\". 2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\". 3. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \\\"EVU\\\". 4. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER table using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\\n7. IF sales customer data NOT empty:\\n    Use sales customer data table entries.\\n   ELSE:\\n    Use net data customer table entries.\\n8. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09A. Use column names: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n9. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address meter.readings@evu.com, file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\\n10. Delete temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_3bd42987-4645-4a82-82fb-30b43695a685"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "7d46a0a9-46b3-4cfb-8e4b-e0ed4acd0d4c",
        "tool_call_id": "call_cre3u1qz",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy decision table into table J09A_temp where the tour starts with J09A.\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\n3. Classify meter reading type. Apply rules: 1. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\". 2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\". 3. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \"EVU\". 4. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \"EVU\".\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER table using EQUNR.\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\n7. IF sales customer data NOT empty:\n    Use sales customer data table entries.\n   ELSE:\n    Use net data customer table entries.\n8. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09A. Use column names: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n9. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address meter.readings@evu.com, file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\n10. Delete temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
